In article <Cq7MyM.5EH@poly.edu>,
Arsen Ray Arachelian <rarachel@poly.edu> wrote:

[description of crypto+stego program deleted]
> The password can be upto 150 characters (that's 1200 bits) however
> this can easily be changed to longer passwords.

Strange, I make 150*7 to be 1050 bits. The actual entropy (real
information) in a 150 character passphrase is considerably lower than
that. You'd be much better off using a hash function like MD5 to
derive reasonable randomness from your passphrase. Perhaps you are
doing this, are you ?

- Andy <asb@cs.nott.ac.uk>
